We are building a Windows (Git Bash) local autonomous multi-bot system using Ollama + SQLite.

PRIMARY GOAL
- Multiple bots (finance/crypto/anything) autonomously generate CODE-ONLY Python via Ollama, execute in persistent sandboxes, stream outputs, and store all chats + runs in SQLite.

HARD REQUIREMENTS
- Ollama API is used directly at http://localhost:11434
  - /api/tags, /api/pull, /api/generate
- Must support streaming generation (stream=true) and print streamed tokens live.
- Must store all messages (system/user/assistant/tool) to SQLite with timestamps.
- Must store all runs to SQLite: code path, stdout/stderr, returncode, duration, score, status.
- Must maintain persistent sandboxes inside repo (NOT temp dirs):
  - sandboxes/<bot_name>/venv/  (per bot venv)
  - sandboxes/<bot_name>/runs/run_XXXX/workspace/  (per run workspace)
- Engine's own environment MUST NOT execute generated code.
  Generated code must always run using the sandbox venv python.exe.
- Must be Windows-compatible:
  - sandbox python path = venv/Scripts/python.exe
  - use pathlib, do not assume POSIX paths
- Dependency installation is OFF by default. If enabled later, it must be allowlist-based and installed only into sandbox venv.

SAFETY
- Treat LLM output as untrusted.
- Enforce strict timeout and maximum log sizes (truncate).
- Never execute shell commands from LLM output.
- Never allow candidate to modify engine files. Candidate runs with cwd set to its workspace.

ARCHITECTURE MODULES (must exist)
- db.py: sqlite schema + helpers
- ollama_client.py: streaming + non-streaming generate, model ensure/pull
- scheduler.py: selects next bot/task to run
- bot_runtime.py: prompt building, generate, validate, execute, score, persist
- validator.py: code-only enforcement + ast.parse
- sandbox.py: ensure bot venv, run candidate with streaming stdout
- main.py: orchestrator loop

DELIVERABLES
- `python main.py` starts orchestrator, creates db, registers default bots, runs bots.
- README with Windows Git Bash instructions.
